    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="424"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d424">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/2239</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Telephone Conversation, by the Assistant
                        Secretary of State</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Long</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-16">September 16,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I called Sir Ronald Campbell on the telephone. He said he had not received from
                    his Government a reply to the question about the search and other details. I
                    suggested to him that I would like to proceed with the negotiations and broach
                    the matter to the German Embassy and Italian Embassy.</p>
                <p>After discussion of the matter, and an explanation of my reason, a part of which
                    was the imminence of some court proceedings to free some of the Italians from
                    confinement, Sir Ronald readily agreed that I do not wait for the reply from the
                    British but that I proceed with the other Governments in a general way.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>B[<hi rend="smallcaps">reckinridge</hi>] L[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ong</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
